[Amit Varma]: exciting episode with these remarkable peoples, let's take a quick commercial break.

00:03:09.400 --> 00:03:13.600
[Amit Varma]: Did you know that Parsis in Mumbai, instead of being left at the Tower of Silence after

00:03:13.600 --> 00:03:19.440
[Amit Varma]: they died, are now cremated? And why? Because a cow fell sick in the early 1990s? Did you

00:03:19.440 --> 00:03:24.080
[Amit Varma]: know that the smog in Delhi is caused by something that farmers in Punjab do and that there's

00:03:24.080 --> 00:03:30.600
[Amit Varma]: no way to stop them? Did you know that there wasn't one gas tragedy in Bhopal but three?

00:03:30.600 --> 00:03:35.560
[Amit Varma]: One of them was seen but two were unseen? Did you know that many well-intentioned government

00:03:35.560 --> 00:03:41.760
[Amit Varma]: policies hurt the people they're supposed to help? Why was demonetization a bad idea?

00:03:41.760 --> 00:03:47.360
[Amit Varma]: How should GST have been implemented? Why are all our politicians so corrupt when not

00:03:47.360 --> 00:03:53.240
[Amit Varma]: all of them are bad people? I'm Amit Verma and in my weekly podcast, The Seen and the

00:03:53.240 --> 00:03:58.840
[Amit Varma]: Unseen, I take a shot at answering all these questions and many more. I aim to go beyond

00:03:58.840 --> 00:04:04.480
[Amit Varma]: the scene and show you the unseen effects of public policy and private action. I speak

00:04:04.480 --> 00:04:08.720
[Amit Varma]: to experts in economics, political philosophy, cognitive neuroscience and constitutional

00:04:08.720 --> 00:04:14.480
[Amit Varma]: law so that the insights can blow not only my mind but also yours. The Seen and the Unseen

00:04:14.480 --> 00:04:20.600
[Amit Varma]: releases every Monday. So do check out the archives and follow the show at seenunseen.in.

00:04:20.600 --> 00:04:26.360
[Amit Varma]: You can also subscribe to The Seen and the Unseen on whatever podcast app you happen

00:04:26.360 --> 00:04:27.360
[Amit Varma]: to prefer.

