[Guest 3]: brides from I read a story in India today, at least two decades back, about how Haryanvi

02:01:16.800 --> 02:01:21.760
[Guest 3]: men are importing Malayali brides because Kerala has, you know, more women than men.

02:01:21.760 --> 02:01:25.640
[Guest 1]: First, they're sharing them and literally treating them like sex slaves.

02:01:25.640 --> 02:01:28.480
[Amit Varma]: So in a household, if there are three brothers, they will share a bride.

02:01:28.480 --> 02:01:32.120
[Amit Varma]: Haryana was, by the way, mentioned in great detail in my fantastic episode with Namita

02:01:32.120 --> 02:01:33.120
[Amit Varma]: Bhandare.

02:01:33.120 --> 02:01:37.880
[Guest 3]: If you guys heard this movie I saw many years back, I don't recall the name very, very disturbing

02:01:37.880 --> 02:01:39.640
[Guest 3]: start Piyush Mishra.

02:01:39.640 --> 02:01:44.000
[Guest 3]: It was about this village where they had run out of women.

02:01:44.000 --> 02:01:49.600
[Guest 3]: And one of the brother, it was a story of some seven brothers, I think, or six or and

02:01:49.600 --> 02:01:54.160
[Guest 3]: one of the brothers went, you know, finally figures out that, you know, there's this woman

02:01:54.160 --> 02:02:02.840
[Guest 3]: who's available and, and she's ready to get married and he goes and turns out that, you

02:02:02.840 --> 02:02:05.440
[Guest 3]: know, she's not a woman, she's a man.

